Constructor Detail

AbstractInterpreterProofModel

protected AbstractInterpreterProofModel(AbstractInterpreterProofNode root,
                                        AbstractProofRuleSet ruleSet)
Allocates a new AbstractInterpreterProofModel with the specified root node. This method automatically calls setMemoryEnabled(boolean) for the root node using its expression and the Expression.containsMemoryOperations() method.

Parameters:
root - the new root item.
ruleSet - the set of proof rules.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if language or root is null.
See Also:

isMemoryEnabled

public boolean isMemoryEnabled()
Returns true if memory operations, as part of the imperative concepts, are used while proving properties of a program. If memory is enabled, the InterpreterProofNode.getStore() method returns the Store at the given node. Otherwise an invalid - usually empty - store will be returned.

Specified by:
isMemoryEnabled in interface InterpreterProofModel
Returns:
true if memory operations are used while evaluating the expression.
See Also:
setMemoryEnabled(boolean), InterpreterProofModel.isMemoryEnabled()

setMemoryEnabled

public void setMemoryEnabled(boolean memoryEnabled)
If memoryEnabled is true the proof model will indicate that memory operations will be used, otherwise the simple configurations should be used and the InterpreterProofNode.getStore() return value will be ignored (and invalid).

Parameters:
memoryEnabled - the new setting.
See Also:
isMemoryEnabled()
